# Episode 05 – Intent Detection and Customer Understanding

In this episode, I taught the AI to identify customer intent.

Instead of only generating responses, the assistant now classifies messages into categories such as NORMAL, REFUND, COMPLAINT, and HUMAN_SUPPORT.

This was a major improvement because businesses often need to take different actions depending on what the customer wants.

For example, a refund request should follow a different process than a complaint or a normal question.

Learning intent detection helped me understand how AI can support business decisions instead of simply answering questions.

Key Learning:
Understanding customer intent is often more valuable than generating a good answer.
